"<p><span class=\"image-wrapper inline-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://ka-perseus-images.s3.amazonaws.com/864cb0fe987e31d5418d40597b61f5b8039cf71d.jpg\" /><span class=\"image-caption\">Female&#39;s face (detail), <em>Sarcophagus of the Spouses</em>, c. 520 B.C.E., Etruscan, painted terracotta, 3 feet 9-1/2 inches x 6 feet 7 inches, found in the Banditaccia necropolis, Cerveteri (Museo Nazionale di Villa Giulia in Rome)</span></span></p>\n"
