"<p><span>The following articles and videos explore seventeenth-century Iran through the reign and legacy of one of its most influential rulers, Shah &#39;Abbas I (reigned 1587&ndash;1629).</span></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><span>Shah &#39;Abbas was a stabilizing force in Iran following a period of civil war and foreign invasion. He strengthened the economy by establishing global trade links between Asia and Europe and revitalized the state religion Shi&rsquo;a Islam which is still practiced today.</span></p>\n"
"\n"
"<p><span>When Shah &#39;Abbas came to power his country was in chaos. Yet, within 11 years he had regained territory lost to his enemies, moved his capital city, and begun a transformation of Iranian society.</span></p>\n"
"\n"
"<h3>Expanding empire</h3>\n"
"\n"
