"<br />\n"
"Hitchcock had praise for his early work, for its &ldquo;many innovations,&quot;&nbsp;but he condemned Wright for a&nbsp;&ldquo;[l]ack of continuity in his development and his unwillingness to absorb the innovations of his contemporaries and his juniors in Europe.&rdquo; Hitchcock insulted Wright further by characterizing him as &ldquo;a rebel by temperament&hellip; [who] refused even the discipline of his own theories.&rdquo; The catalogue calls Wright a &ldquo;half-modern&rdquo; throwback, one of the &ldquo;last representatives of Romanticism.&rdquo;&nbsp;Wright responded by denigrating European Modernism as an &ldquo;evil crusade,&rdquo; a manifestation of &ldquo;totalitarianism.&rdquo;</p>\n"
"\n"
"<h3>A fellowship and a commission</h3>\n"
"\n"
