msgid "It looks like you are passing the number 180 as the second argument in the calls to ellipse(). You're right--the y location of the eyes is 180. However, in the interest of keeping the code clean, let's have a variable store the expression (centerY-20) instead, and then pass that variable as the second argument in the ellipse() calls. The value of this expression is also 180, but if we ever decide to move the moose up or down, the eyes will move the corresponding amount as well."
