msgid ""
"Whether in the real world or a cliche fantasy one, systems of equations are key to solving super-important issues like \"the make-up of change in a troll's pocket\" or \"how can order the right amount of potato chips for a King's party.\"  Join us as we cover (and practice with examples and exercises) all of the major ways of solving a system: graphically, elimination, and substitution.  This tutorial will also help you think about when system might have no solution or an infinite number of solutions.  Very, very exciting stuff!\n"
